Do: "explore the relationships between these quartets—perhaps how they might combine or transition into each other", specifically for the 3 quartets:

{Art, Evolution, Energy, Complexity}
{Creativity, Horizons, Design, Autonomy}
{Infinity, Recursion, Work, Freedom}

Where {Art, Evolution, Energy, Complexity} = "1∀" (art is the 1 thing in everything, evolution also pertains to everything, it's the trace of history in everything, energy/information is also in everything, and complexity is the "1 algorithm in everything")
What could be other common feature, probably not based on the same basis of "1 in everything" but creative variations on this theme, in the other quartets?

In this list, how many possible combinations of 3 quartets can we have, where all vertices appear only once?

Complete List of Quartets
#	Environment Pair	Self Pair	Quartet
1	Infinity (1), Recursion (11)	Work (12), Freedom (3)	{Infinity, Recursion, Work, Freedom}
2	Creativity (2), Art (4)	Design (10), Energy (7)	{Creativity, Art, Design, Energy}
3	Creativity (2), Horizons (5)	Design (10), Autonomy (8)	{Creativity, Horizons, Design, Autonomy}
4	Creativity (2), Recursion (11)	Design (10), Freedom (3)	{Creativity, Recursion, Design, Freedom}
5	Art (4), Evolution (6)	Energy (7), Complexity (9)	{Art, Evolution, Energy, Complexity} ← your example
6	Art (4), Recursion (11)	Energy (7), Freedom (3)	{Art, Recursion, Energy, Freedom}
